[description]
GNU Zi is a lightweight text editor descended from GNU Zile with
suitable functionality for basic editing. Compared to Zile, the
Lisp Engine has been removed, but since it is implemented entirely
in Lua, it is easily extended and customized.

/then go to/
Exit status is 0 if OK, 1 if it cannot start up, for example because
of an invalid command-line argument, and 2 if it crashes or runs out
of memory.

[files]
~/.zi \(em user's Zi init file

[author]
Zi was written by Reuben Thomas and Gary V. Vaughan, based on the
Lua version of Zile.

